The advice was given to the Russian President by doctors after he suffered “a sharp sickness, weakness and dizziness’’ after appearing on video with advisers a few days ago, according to the Telegram channel General SVR - purportedly run by a Kremlin source. The account said: "[When Putin began] preparing to answer the questions of the Russian citizens in late June-early July … his doctors advised him not to make any lengthy public appearances in the near future. The indefinite postponement of the [question-answer exchange] is due to the unstable health of Vladimir Putin. The president’s indisposition has recently become increasingly difficult to conceal.” FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...